"Simple example of how to use a layer
" this file can be loaded with :call keybindings#Source(expand('%'))
"
" ~ in the layer name says to not print
" informations when activating the layer
km(n) <C-q> "~C-q"    <Layer>
" shortcuts belonging to a layer shall be defined like that
km(n) <Esc> ":Exit"   <ExitLayer>
km(n) <Up>  ":Up"   <Up>
" however it is possible to define keybinding with layer name
km(n) <Down>  "~C-q:Up"   <Up>
